Description: LDAP daemon backed by the local POSIX user and group database
 pwldapd is a read-only LDAP server (RFC 4510) that exposes the local
 POSIX user and group database over the LDAP protocol. It reads accounts
 through the system's name-service switch (NSS) layer and presents them
 as standard posixAccount/inetOrgPerson and posixGroup entries.
 .
 Bind requests are authenticated via PAM. Anonymous binds are accepted.
 TLS (LDAPS) is supported. The daemon is intended for use on a single
 host where LDAP-aware applications — such as SSH, sudo, or web servers —
 need to look up local accounts without a separate directory service.
 .
 The daemon does not persist any state and does not support write
 operations.
